      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Features of LTX-2 19B Distilled FP8 a"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LTX-2 19B Distilled FP8 a leverages model distillation and FP8 quantization to achieve a smaller footprint without significant accuracy loss. Key aspects include a 19-billion parameter architecture optimized for inference, FP8 support for faster computation on compatible hardware, and distilled weights that reduce memory usage by up to 50% compared to FP16 baselines. This makes it suitable for API endpoints requiring high throughput with constrained resources."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating LTX-2 19B Distilled FP8 a into API Infrastructure"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To integrate this model, use standard API frameworks like FastAPI or Flask with ONNX Runtime or TensorRT for FP8 acceleration. Ensure your serving environment supports FP8 operations—common in NVIDIA GPUs with Ada Lovelace or Hopper architectures. Implement batching for concurrent requests and set up health checks to monitor model loading and inference latency. For example, configure a REST endpoint that accepts JSON payloads with text inputs and returns predictions, handling errors gracefully for robustness."
          }
        ]
